# Code owners — automatic reviewer assignment.
#
# Syntax: <pattern> <space-separated owners>
# Most-specific match wins.
# See: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositories-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners

# Default — BDFL gets pinged on anything not otherwise covered.
*                                @ai3stack

# Content (bulk of PRs land here)
/content/                        @ai3stack
/content/en-US/                  @ai3stack

# Governance / policy — must be reviewed by BDFL
/GOVERNANCE.md                   @ai3stack
/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md              @ai3stack
/LICENSE                         @ai3stack
/SECURITY.md                     @ai3stack
/docs/DECISIONS.md               @ai3stack

# Schema — touching this is an RFC-level change
/docs/PROMPT_SCHEMA.md           @ai3stack
/scripts/validate_prompts.py     @ai3stack

# CI — security-sensitive
/.github/workflows/              @ai3stack
/.github/CODEOWNERS              @ai3stack

# Once Committers exist, replace @ai3stack above with team handle
# (e.g. @ai3stack/committers) and adjust per-area as appropriate.
